# File Size Limit

Files should be **700 lines or fewer**. When you create or edit a file that exceeds this threshold, flag it and propose a split.

## When writing or editing code

- Before finishing work on a file, check its line count.
- If a file is over 700 lines, proactively suggest or perform a refactor to split it into smaller, cohesive modules.
- Prefer splitting along domain boundaries (e.g. separate controllers for different resource types, separate hooks for different concerns).

## When reviewing existing code

- If you encounter a file over 700 lines during normal work, note it as a candidate for future refactoring.
- Do not block unrelated work to refactor, but do mention it.
